        "text": "<@U04E5QAD6DD> though not hyped at all at this point, and perhaps because of it, I've found some corners of VR to be that exact kind of magical other-world.  For example, my son and I were playing Roblox and stumbled on an experience:  cute little mushroom fantasy village eerily polished by Roblox standards.  When we went into the the correct mushroom house, we discovered the world was front for the dance club underground.  The place was packed.  The avatars were all dressed up.  And it was a lot of fun.",
